Nakakapikon 'yung comment ni Lisa Takeuchi Cullen. Mas pipiliin niyang wala at all? Jeez, and it's not like people are limiting their actions to that. At least they got so many women to participate. Has that happened before? Umm, no. Ang pa-intellectual.

Raising awareness nga eh. To do that, a series of campaigns and projects need to be successfully noticed by the public. Instead of debating about whether it was effective or not, why not think of other projects? Instead of telling people to boycott the campaign, start your own.

Haha, wala lang. Nairita lang ako. Cullen pa last name niya, go figure. Hehe.

I forgot that I made a promise to be happier.

Everything is going to be alright. There's love in the world.

Ok, random statements.

Boracay was fun. Super. But in a "Parteeeey!!!!" way, not in a, I-feel-so-amazing-and-well-rested kind of way. Quezon was different. Meeting Tito's family was different. Reconnecting with my best dark friend was different. It wasn't better than Bora. Bora was everything I expected it to be and it was fun and exciting and unbelievably chaotic. Pero Quezon, on the other hand, was peaceful and romantic and classic. And it was a whole new experiece for me, from the Senor, to the Salubong up until the Buhusan. Can't wait to go back there. :) As in I wanna live there and eat and drink and dilly dally with my friends. Haha.

Sorry, tamad ako mag-blog. There were just too many events. 

But anyway, now I'm ready to get back to work. 

This summer's itinerary:

TONIGHT WE SLEEP will be recording their album so we'll be taking care of the paperwork and we'll be supervising the process kasi pasaway sila (but they're brilliant and sweet)

The Manger's third production, DITO TAYO SA DILIM will be pushing through next month, and I'm DQ's APM (alongside the beautiful Kiki "Bakiki" Isaac (she'll hate me for this. haha)) so exag pre-prod na 'to.

O film. I dunno what I'm gonna do for it yet, but I've already attended some of the meetings and I've been helping Jan a lot so it's gonna take up a lot of my time, too.

ANYWAY!!

Tune in to NU107.5 tomorrow at 9pm and jam with TONIGHT WE SLEEP!! Also, same time, same station, PASCALENE will perform an acoustic set on April 20!

I heart Mary Moon. :)

Just take my hand and we'll make it, I swear.

Dahil sa patuloy na pag-alis ng kanilang mga asawa upang sumabak sa digmaan, isang grupo ng mga maybahay sa pamumuno ni Lysistrata ang nagkaisa sa isang sagradong kasunduan: tatanggi silang makipagtalik sa kanilang mga asawa hangga't hindi pa natatapos ang digmaan ng Atena at Sparta. Kakayanin kaya ng mga babae ang paghihintay sa kapayapaan? Kakayanin kaya ng mga lalaki ang pagtalikod sa karangalan ng digmaan? Sino ang unang bibigay? Panoorin at alamin!

I'm so nervous for One True Love. I've never made a film before, and we (cast and crew) have never really experienced making a film that's just ours.

Right now, my major concerns as Production Manager are:

1. Getting the cast there
2. Shooting in just 3 days
3. Pulling off the set changes
4. Market!!

And other than my concerns as PM, I just really want this film to be good. I want it to matter not just to the people who made it but to those who will watch it also. I don't want this film to look like a half-baked product of boredom, even though it kind of is. (not the half-baked part) Gah. I'm so nervous.

So in line with this:

If you know venues (bars, cafes, schools, etc.) that feature indie films, please give me contact numbers, or kahit names lang of venues, please? THANK YOU.

And it's never too late to help! Leave a comment if you want to help by being a PA, and you might even get a chance to have a cameo! Haha. :D

Shooting dates will be on Sundays of June (except the 8th) and the first Sunday of July. THANK YOU!
I'm beginning to have a clearer picture of the kind of life I want to live, and the people I want to be in it.

"It was a Thursday morning. You were wearing that ratty little Dartmouth t-shirt you look so good in. The one with the hole in the back of the neck. You had just washed your hair and smelled like some kind of flower. I was running late for surgery. You said you were going to see me later. Then you leaned to me. You put your hand on my chest. And you kissed me. Soft. It was quick, kind of like a habit. You know like we'd do it every day for the rest of our lives. Then you went back to reading the newspaper and I went to work. That was the last time we kissed."

Lately, silence has been my greatest enemy, and constant companion. I need it, but I don't want it. But I get it.

I love silence. I've never appreciated it more.

I hate silence. It brings about internal chaos.

Watched The Prestige the other day. I was disappointed, kasi once again, the movie could have been grand, pero sinira nung ibang parts. Here's why:

1. The last conversation between the two was pretty much just a repeat of the thesis statement which was delivered almost every other scene of the movie. Lacked power.
2. Parang medjo may mga parts na di na kailangan.
3. It was too damn long that you end up figuring out what was gonna happen after and hour and twenty minuets which is how long the movie should have been na lang.
4. Foreshadowing wasn't subtle.

Pero okay naman siya. It was creative and interesting. I love Hugh and Scarlett (close?? haha) and the rest of the cast. I give it a.............7.5. Moulin Rouge being a ten. (mahal ko si Baz Luhrman, okay? And yes, Martin, I will get over it.)

Anyway, I'm looking forward to a lot of movies ngayon. Haha. I need money. I'm so broke.
